(1, 'THREE-TIME WINNER LGU TANAY', 'three-time-winner-lgu-tanay', '<p>For the third consecutive time, the Municipal Government of Tanay, Rizal was adjudged as the Most Outstanding Local Government Unit (LGU) - Class A Municipality category, during the awarding rites of the 2018 National Literacy Awards - Regional Level - Search for Outstanding LGUs held last August 14, 2018 in Cainta, Rizal. The search is being held every two years and Tanay was also the 2014 and 2016 regional winner in the same category.</p><p>Tanay’s win automatically qualified it to the National Level, with initial assessment of the selection committee placing Tanay in the Top 5 among all entries throughout the country.</p><p>The local government of Tanay has been implementing programs that have benefitted in-school and out-of-school youth, ALS learners, persons with disability, jail inmates, senior citizens, women, indigenous peoples (IPs), farmers, children at risk, entrepreneurs and the community.</p><p>Among the various literacy programs that Tanay has been vigorously implementing are Karunungan ng mga Katutubo sa Bulubundukin ng Tanay (KABULTAN), KalyeRunungan, Continuing Education Program for ALS learners, Bigay Kinabukasan sa Selda and Panitikan Ugnayan Gawain Alituntunin ng Dumagat Remontado (PUGAD) project.</p><p>There are also trainings conducted by the municipality, Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Trainings, Technical skills education (TESDA), sustainable farm field school, all year round tour guide training and trainings for IPs to serve as community health workers.</p><p>Mayor Rex Manuel Tanjuatco, only in his first term of office, is strongly committed in providing quality education for all sectors of the society most especially for those in the far-flung areas of Tanay.</p><p>Further, the municipality supports a school program for the Muslim (Madrasah), it has also opened several new schools outside the poblacion and, under a Memorandum of Agreement with the University of Rizal System, founded the construction of an annex of the university at the Tanay town proper.</p><p>In view, Mayor Tanjuatco’s guiding principle that “A literate citizenry is the key to a progressive community”, has served well the municipality and the beneficiaries of its various education-centered programs and projects.</p>', '#WINNERS', 'published', '2018-10-08 12:12:12', '2018-10-08 12:12:00', '2018-10-12 08:29:08', NULL, 1, 1),
(2, 'LGU TANAY CONDUCTS ORIENTATION ON DRR CCA TO THE SK OFFICIALS', 'lgu-tanay-conducts-orientation-on-drr-cca-to-the-sk-officials', '<p>The global trend of disaster nowadays urge every members of the society to keep abreast with the four thematic areas of DRRM namely, (1) Disaster Prevention and Mitigation; (2) Disaster Preparedness; (3) Disaster Response; and (4) Disaster Rehabilitation and Recovery. The MDRRMO and its partner agencies, through the initiative of Mayor RM Tanjuatco, conducted an orientation on DRR CCA to the Sangguniang Kabataan officials of 19 barangays last Saturday, July 14 at the Dumagat Hall, University of Rizal System, Tanay Main Campus.</p><p><img src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/article-photos/orientation-on-DRR-CCA-SK-TANAY.jpg\" alt=\"orientation on DRR CCA SK TANAY\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" data-mce-src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/article-photos/orientation-on-DRR-CCA-SK-TANAY.jpg\"></p><p>Engr. Carlos Inofre Jr discussed to them thoroughly the four thematic areas of DRR and the basic concept of climate change adaptation. Present also to give an inspirational message is Mayor Tanjuatco. Also, to address other related topics were fire officer Alan Martinez and SPO4 Manuel Padlan. The SK participants were group into six, and each group were given time to prepare for their Programs, Projects and Activities related to DRR CCA as part of the workshop. Each group performed first their yell then the PPA\'s.</p>', '#LGUTANAY', 'published', '2018-09-18 14:05:43', '2018-09-05 10:30:00', '2018-10-12 07:23:14', NULL, 1, 1),
(3, 'AADAC PHL INC GAVE A PLAQUE OF APPRECIATION TO MAYOR RM TANJUATCO', 'aadac-phl-inc-gave-a-plaque-of-appreciation-to-mayor-rm-tanjuatco', '<p>The Association of Antidrug Abuse Coalitions of the Philippines Inc gave a Plaque of Appreciation to Mayor Rex Manuel C. Tanjuatco for the unrelenting support given to AADAC PHL Inc and Affiliate Coalitions of Tanay during the 1st AADAC PHL Inc. National Conference at Bellevue Hotel, Filinvest, Alabang, Muntinlupa City on 28 May 2018.<span id=\"_mce_caret\" data-mce-bogus=\"1\" data-mce-type=\"format-caret\"></span></p>', '#APPRECIATIONTOMAYORRMTANJUATCO', 'published', '2018-09-19 05:48:37', '2018-09-20 14:50:00', '2018-10-12 07:22:32', NULL, 1, 2),
(4, 'TANAY RECEIVED OUTSTANDING LITERACY AWARD', 'tanay-received-outstanding-literacy-award', '<p><img src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/article-photos/literacy-award-2018-tanay.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"232\" alt=\"\" data-mce-src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/article-photos/literacy-award-2018-tanay.jpg\"></p><p>Recently the Municipality of Tanay marks the national awarding of the Literacy Coordinating Council Outstanding Local Government Unit for being one of the five LGU’s(1st to 3rd Class Category) in the whole Philippines to be included in the top Literacy programs and projects implementations for its constituents under the leadership of Mayor Rex Manuel C. Tanjuatco. <br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p><p>Present in the awarding are Usec. Lorna Dig-Dino of Deped, LCC Officials,&nbsp; Ms. Imelda M. Asuncion - PSDS, Tanay IA, Mr. Ernesto B. Discutido - PSDS, Tanay IB, Dr. Armando A. Ponce- PSDS, Tanay IIB, Mr. Benito C. Picones, Education Program Supervisor from Deped Rizal, LGU Staff and Mayor RM C. Tanjuatco</p><p>The awarding was held last September 6, 2018 at Hotel Supreme in Baguio City where other awardees for different categories of the Literacy Coordinating Council National Literacy Award were conducted.</p>', '#OutstandingLiteracyAward ', 'published', '2018-09-20 01:18:28', '2018-09-07 00:00:00', '2018-10-12 07:22:42', NULL, 1, 1),
(5, 'THE MUNICIPALITY OF TANAY NOW HAS ITS 20TH BARANGAY', 'the-municipality-of-tanay-now-has-its-20th-barangay', '<p><img src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/article-photos/brgy-madilay-dilay-tanay.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"232\" alt=\"\" data-mce-src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/article-photos/brgy-madilay-dilay-tanay.jpg\"></p><p>The municipality of Tanay now has its 20th Barangay From the previews 19 Barangay,</p><p>Tanay now has its 20th Barangay after the successful plebiscite creating Barangay Madilay-dilay last July 28, 2018, in Barangay Sampaloc. Barangay Madilay-dilay has its own natural tourist destination, from Mt. Kalbaryo, Dambuhalang Ilog, Madilay-dilay Cave, Langit-langitan and its Century Old Balete Tree.</p>', '#20thBarangay', 'draft', '2018-09-20 01:23:22', '2018-08-29 00:00:00', '2018-10-12 10:08:58', NULL, 1, 1),
(6, 'CBDRRM TRAINING OF TRAINERS', 'cbdrrm-training-of-trainers', '<p>The MDRRMO of Tanay in cooperation and partnership with the Office of Civil Defense (OCD) in CALABARZON Region and Department of Interior Local Government (DILG) conducted the training of trainers on June 26-30, 2018, at Tanay Municipal Hall activity area. The said activity aims to develop a pool of instructors to cater nineteen Barangays of Tanay both Poblacion and in the Upland Communities to have their own CBDRRM and to understand the underlying concept CBDRM in the context of the Disaster Management Cycle.</p><p>There were 30 participants from the LGU, members of MDDRM council, DepEd, NGOs, who successfully passed the training and evaluation. Community-based disaster risk management (CBDRM) is a process, which leads to a locally \"owned\" strategy for disaster preparedness and risk reduction. This course explores the different dimensions of the CBDRM approach and has been designed to improve the effectiveness of specialist and non-specialist professionals in disaster response, helping them to link the disasters with risk reduction and development in a sustainable manner. This course can be made modular to focus on different topics like community-based disaster preparedness, community emergency response teams, community contingency planning, and organizational level disaster preparedness. It also introduces the significance, nature and scope of CBDRRM and further delves into understanding the essentials of preparedness planning. Further, it explores the process of capacity and vulnerability analysis, participatory planning and risk assessment tools, predictability, forecasting and early warning system, use of sphere standards in community-based disaster preparedness, family level preparedness and relief and rescue, long-term disaster mitigation and preparedness measures and asset building for the same.</p>', '6', 'published', '2018-09-22 15:15:45', '2018-08-07 09:05:00', '2018-09-22 23:43:32', NULL, 1, 1),
(7, 'INDEPENDENCE DAY 2018 CUM STATE OF THE MUNICIPALITY ADDRESS', 'independence-day-2018-cum-state-of-the-municipality-address', '<p>The downpour caused by Habagat didn’t hinder the people of Tanay from celebrating 120years of solemn and joyous Independence Day, just as our Hon. Mayor Rex Manuel C.Tanjuatco said, “It was solemn because we are all aware that our independence came at a very steep price, and joyous because we are a free country and there are no foreign invaders that oppress our rights…”.It was indeed a rainy season, but our nationalism continuously to ignites we celebrate this very occasion.</p><p>The celebration started with a morning mass in San Ildefonso Parish Church followed by a short parade to the venue, warmly welcoming the distinguished guests, Tanay LGU employees, and members of the different sectors from the community of Tanay. After the tableau, performed by the students of Tanay National Highschool, our Hon. Vice Mayor Jaime B. Vista gave his warm opening speech. The ceremonial entrance of the colors (our national flag) gave a patriotic meaning to the singing of the Philippine National Anthem, led by SRBMES Choir.</p><p>Together with his greetings and remarks, our Hon. Mayor Rex Manuel C. Tanjuatco also disclosed all the achievements he has made for Tanay in his ‘State of the Municipal Address,’ covering all the accomplishments and awards in his almost two years of service and his goals towards the more sustainable development of Tanay. He acknowledged several events and accomplishments that Tanay has obtained such as, livelihood development, agricultural development, achievements in health services, infrastructure developments, achievements in peace and order, achievements in environmental management, local economic development and more. On his ending note, our Mayor Rex Manuel said, “We (LGU) want a continued rise of Tanay, all belong, all benefits.” With this, Tanay has the momentum for continuous and sustainable growth.</p><p>The last part of the Independence Day Program is the ribbon cutting ceremony for the Blessing and the Inauguration of the Newly Built ATM Machine of Land Bank in the Municipal Compound.&nbsp; To make the cash on demand transactions with Land Bank faster and easier, not only for the employees of the municipal but also for the people of Tanay.</p><p>Indeed, Tanay has grown, reaching more milestones as times goes by, but we have to still keep in mind the sacrifices that our heroes and ancestors have done for us to have the independence that we continue to celebrate and the happiness that comes from that freedom. Happy Independence Day!</p>', '#IndependenceDay', 'published', '2018-09-22 15:34:42', '2018-06-25 00:05:00', '2018-10-03 22:54:48', NULL, 1, 1),
(8, 'MAYOR RM TANJUATCO GRACED THE GRADUATION OF INMATES UNDER ALS', 'mayor-rm-tanjuatco-graced-the-graduation-of-inmates-under-als', '<p>Recently, Tanay BJMP under the leadership of Mayor Rex Manuel C. Tanjuatco graced the graduation of inmates under Alternative Learning System</p><p>of DEPED Tanay on which some of them graduated from Elementary and Secondary Education. The Local Government Unit of Tanay has taken responsibility for providing primary literacy program to inmates from 2011 to present.</p>', '8', 'published', '2018-09-22 15:50:06', '2018-08-01 00:00:00', '2018-10-03 22:53:17', NULL, 1, 1),
(9, 'LGU TANAY RECOGNIZES TOP-PERFORMING BARANGAYS', '', '<p>In amanner similar to the Department of Interior and Local Government’s Seal of Good Local Governance, the municipality of Tanay gave recognition to its barangays that performed well in 2016 in different components of governance and public service during&nbsp;<em>Gabi ng Parangal 2017,&nbsp;</em>the culminating activity of the 7<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;Hane Festival held last November 12, 2017.</p><p>Highlighting the integrity, accountability, transparency, and community involvement manifested by its 19 barangays, the municipal government adopted the SGLG into the Seal of Good Barangay Governance. The SGBG is primarily aimed at determining the level of performance of every barangay in Disaster Preparedness, Social Protection, Environmental Management, Peace and Order, and Tourism and People-Friendliness, regardless of their population size and income. Parallel with the SGLG’s mechanisms on evaluation, the local government also created an assessment team that conducted on-site and document validations in both poblacion and upland barangays.</p><p>After complying with the necessary documentations and reaching the required mark, the following barangays received plaques of recognition in the different components:</p><p><strong><br></strong></p><p><strong>Seal of Tourism and People-Friendliness</strong></p><ol><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Sampaloc</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of San Isidro</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Wawa</li></ol><p><strong>Seal of Good Peace and Order</strong></p><ol><li>Sangguniang Barangay of San Isidro</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Wawa</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Katipunan-Bayani</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Daraitan</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Cuyambay</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Tandang Kutyo</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Plaza Aldea</li></ol><p><strong>Seal of Good Environmental Management</strong></p><ol><li>Sangguniang Barangay of San Isidro and Sangguniang Barangay of Wawa</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Katipunan-Bayani</li></ol><p><strong>Seal of Good Social Protection</strong></p><ol><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Katipunan-Bayani</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of San Isidro</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Wawa</li></ol><p><strong>Seal of Good Disaster Preparedness</strong></p><ol><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Katipunan-Bayani</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Wawa</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of San Isidro</li><li>Sangguniang Barangay of Cuyambay</li></ol><p><br></p><p>Though there was no awardee in the Financial Administration component (hence no eventual SGBG seal and P500,000 cash incentive recipient), Mayor Rex&nbsp; Manuel C. Tanjuatco still rewarded the top-performing barangays namely San Isidro, Wawa, Katipunan-Bayani, and Sampaloc with P100,000 worth of projects.</p><p>Aside from local government officials and employees, council members of all barangays in Tanay, and other awardees, DILG-CALABARZON Regional Director Manuel Q. Gotis, was also present during the event as guest of honor. In his message, he lauded the municipal government for this initiative and congratulated Tanay forbagging a back-to-back SGLG award. Moreover, he also expressed his confidence in the municipality for adhering to themandate of the local government code and other national rules and regulations, and encouraged all the barangays to keep up with their best practices to be able to garner the much coveted SGBG.</p>', '#TopPerfomingBarangay\'s', 'published', '2018-09-22 15:56:31', '2017-12-13 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(10, 'HEALTH AND WELLNESS FOR SENIOR CITIZEN A SUCCESS', 'health-and-wellness-for-senior-citizen-a-success', '<p><img src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/article-photos/senior-wellness/tanay-senior-wellness.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"166\" alt=\"\"><br></p><p>Mayor RM Tanjuatco welcomed the Senior Citizens as they took part of the Health and Wellness Program organized by POPCOM Region IV and Provincial Health Office in cooperation with MSWD Tanay, Office of the Senior Citizen Affairs and Municipal Population Office.</p><p>Over 100 Senior Citizens from different barangays of Tanay benefited from free Zumba with lectures and check-up on Oral Health care and pneumonia.</p>', '10', 'published', '2018-09-22 16:11:19', '2017-11-21 00:00:00', '2018-10-03 22:55:11', NULL, 1, 1),
(11, 'TANAY LGU PUSHES HELP FOR LOCAL FISHERMEN', '', '<p><img src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/Images-for-Pages/tanay-local-fishermen.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"166\" alt=\"\"><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p><p>Mayor Rex Manuel C. Tanjuatco together with Councilor Ivan Allen Tongohan and Municipal Agriculture Office, Head Mr.&nbsp;Romeo Cruz&nbsp;led the distribution of Solar Lamp for the fishermen that will help them on their fishing activity during at night and fish stall, fish cladding was also given for the proper presentation of their fish harvests. Mayor Rex Manuel C. Tanjuatco also inspects the newly received farm tractor for the local farmers of Tanay in coordination with the National Government.</p><p><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p>', '11', 'published', '2018-09-22 16:21:37', '2017-10-10 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(12, 'TANAY HOSTS THE 58TH REGULAR SANGGUNIANG PANLALAWIGAN SESSION', 'tanay-hosts-the-58th-regular-sangguniang-panlalawigan-session', '<p>As Tanay\'s being the home of nature and adventure destination the Sangguniang Panlalawigan of Rizal headed by Vice Governor, Hon. Reynaldo H. San Juan, Jr., M.D. Held its 58th regular session in Martessem Hotel and Resort located in Sitio Mayagay, Tanay, Rizal.</p><p><img src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/Images-for-Pages/tanay-sangguniang-panlalawigan-session.jpg\" width=\"377\" height=\"250\" alt=\"\" data-mce-src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/Images-for-Pages/tanay-sangguniang-panlalawigan-session.jpg\"></p><p>Mayor Rex Manuel C. Tanjuatco together with the members of the Sangguniang Bayan headed by Vice Mayor Jimmy Vista welcome the Provincial Delegation as they arrived in the event area.</p>', '12', 'published', '2018-09-22 16:24:37', '2018-10-10 00:00:00', '2018-10-12 08:29:02', NULL, 1, 1),
(13, 'TANAY MDRRMC IS 2017 REG’L GAWAD KALASAG 2ND BEST LDRRM COUNCIL', '', '<p>Tanay MDRRM Council received another Regional Gawad Kalasag nod as 2nd Place Best Local DRRM Council (1st-3rd Class Municipality) during the awarding rites held August 24 at the Development Academy of the Philippines in Tagaytay City.</p><p><img src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/Images-for-Pages/gawad-kalasag-tanay-2017.jpg\" width=\"374\" height=\"250\" alt=\"\"><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p><p>Vice Mayor Jaime Vista received the trophy and cash prize worth P30,000 on behalf of the Council.</p><p>It was the third straight year that the Council has won in the said contest. The Council was also last year’s second place winner in the said category, while it placed first in 2015 during its initial try.</p><p>Carmona MDRRM Council did a repeat of last year’s performance as it re-emerged as first place winner. Meanwhile, Pagsanjan MDRRMC, a first-time entrant, landed as third best in the category.</p><p>During the traditional flag raising ceremonies, Tanay MDRRM Council Chairperson, Mayor Rex Manuel C. Tanjuatco, expressed his gratitude to all Council members for their active involvement in its programs, projects, and activities (PPAs).</p><p>He also rallied the entire LGU workforce to continuously support the Council’s efforts in the Four Thematic Areas of disaster risk reduction and management, namely: Prevention and Mitigation, Preparedness, Response, and Recovery and Rehabilitation.</p>', '13', 'published', '2018-09-22 16:26:24', '2017-10-10 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(14, 'TANAY LGU HELPS PWD STUDENTS', '', '<p><img src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/Images-for-Pages/tanay-pwd-students.jpg\" width=\"553\" height=\"250\" alt=\"\"><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p><p>Mayor Rex Manuel C. Tanjuatco, MSWD Tanay, Treasury Office and members of the Sanggunian Bayan witness the Pay-out ceremony for the monthly pension of the PWD students.&nbsp;Present in the pay-out ceremony are the parents and guardians of the student beneficiaries.</p>', '14', 'published', '2018-09-22 16:27:46', '2017-10-10 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(15, 'CONGRATULATIONS ALTERNATIVE LEARNING SYSTEM FOLK DANCERS TANAY I', '', '<p>Congratulations Alternative Learning System folk dancers Tanay I for winning 2nd place in the Division Festival of Talent last September 19, 2017</p><p><img src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/Images-for-Pages/als-tanay.jpg\" width=\"379\" height=\"250\" alt=\"\"><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p>', '15', 'published', '2018-09-22 16:28:52', '2017-10-10 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(20, 'JOIN NOW! TANAY PHOTOGRAPHY CONTEST 2018', 'join-now-tanay-photography-contest-2018', '<p>Tanay Photography Contest 2018</p><p>This year 8th Tanay Hane Festival 2018 will highlight the beauty of Tanay from amateur photographer to pro-photographers. Three categories are open to all locals and tourist of Tanay.</p><p>Prizes:&nbsp;<br>Grand Prize&nbsp;<br>Winner Category: SELFIE: Php 5,000<br>Winner Category: GROUPIE: Php 7,000<br>Winner Category: Tanay : Php 10,000</p>', 'Tanay photography ', 'published', '2018-10-11 22:27:14', '2018-09-28 09:00:00', '2018-10-12 08:29:53', NULL, 1, 2),
