(22, 'SA LAHAT NG MGA TAONG MAY KAPANSANAN NA WALA PANG PWD ID CARD AT PURCHASE BOOKLET MAGSADYA LAMANG SA', 'sa-lahat-ng-mga-taong-may-kapansanan-na-wala-pang-pwd-id-card-at-purchase-booklet-magsadya-lamang-sa', '<p>Sa lahat ng mga taong may kapansanan na wala pang PWD ID Card at Purchase Booklet magsadya lamang sa tanggapan ng MWSD upang ma – assess at maisyuhan ng PWD ID Card at Purchase Booklet. Dalhin ang mga sumusunod:</p><p>1. &nbsp;Barangay Certificate of Residency</p><p>2. &nbsp;1 pc. 2x2 ID picture</p><p>3. &nbsp;2 pcs. 1x1 ID picture</p><p>4. Medical Certificate kung mayroon</p>', '#PWD', 'published', '2018-10-11 22:32:54', '2018-09-21 07:00:00', '2018-10-12 07:21:31', NULL, 1, 3),
(24, 'NOMINATIONS FOR PANATA 2018 IS NOW OPEN', 'nominations-for-panata-2018-is-now-open', '<p>Nomination for PANATA&nbsp; “ 2018 Parangal sa Natatanging Anak ng Tanay” (PANATA) is open to all individuals from the following fields: Public Service, Entrepreneurship, Education, Arts and Culture, Professionals. Any person or organization may nominate one or more individuals subject to the guidelines and criteria. However, members of the PANATA - Screening Committee, officials and employees of the municipal government of Tanay are not eligible for nomination.</p>', '#Panata 2018', 'published', '2018-10-11 22:38:48', '2018-09-21 07:00:00', '2018-10-12 08:30:00', NULL, 1, 3),
(25, 'LGU TANAY RECOGNIZES TOP-PERFORMING BARANGAYS', '', '<p>n amanner similar to the Department of Interior and Local Government’s Seal of Good Local Governance, the municipality of Tanay gave recognition to its barangays that performed well in 2016 in different components of governance and public service during&nbsp;<em>Gabi ng Parangal 2017,&nbsp;</em>the culminating activity of the 7<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;Hane Festival held last November 12, 2017.</p><p>Highlighting the integrity, accountability, transparency, and community involvement manifested by its 19 barangays, the municipal government adopted the SGLG into the Seal of Good Barangay Governance. The SGBG is primarily aimed at determining the level of performance of every barangay in Disaster Preparedness, Social Protection, Environmental Management, Peace and Order, and Tourism and People-Friendliness, regardless of their population size and income. Parallel with the SGLG’s mechanisms on evaluation, the local government also created an assessment team that conducted on-site and document validations in both poblacion and upland barangays.</p>', 'LGU FOR TOP', 'published', '2018-10-11 22:44:49', '2017-12-13 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 1, 0),
