rism partners and investors from the business sector and non-government organizations</p><p><a href=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/for-visitors/tourist-information/2015-07-10-03-46-25/tanay-hane-festival\">http://tanay.gov.ph/for-visitors/tourist-information/2015-07-10-03-46-25/tanay-hane-festival</a></p><p><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p>', 'festival', 'Hane Festival', 1, 2, '2018-10-03 10:58:18', 5, 1),
(15, 'TANAY RODEO FESTIVAL', 'tanay-rodeo-festival', '<p>To promote and market the town’s cattle and agri-eco tourism not only within the&nbsp; municipality but also in the CALABARZON&nbsp; region, the Municipal Government of Tanay holds Tanay Rodeo every third week of January each year.</p><p>The festival is also in line with the celebration of Tanay Town Fiesta. It is participated by professionals and rodeo enthusiasts, and veterinary/animal science students from renowned universities in the country</p><p><a href=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/for-visitors/tourist-information/2015-07-10-03-46-25/tanay-rodeo-festival\">http://tanay.gov.ph/for-visitors/tourist-information/2015-07-10-03-46-25/tanay-rodeo-festival</a></p><p><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p>', 'festival', '#TanayRodeoFestival', 1, 3, '2018-10-03 10:58:18', 5, 1),
(16, 'JOIN NOW! TANAY PHOTOGRAPHY CONTEST 2018', 'join-now-tanay-photography-contest-2018', '<p>Tanay Photography Contest 2018</p><p><br>This year 8th Tanay Hane Festival 2018 will highlight the beauty of Tanay from amateur photographer to pro-photographers. Three categories are open to all locals and tourist of Tanay.</p><p><br>Who are qualified to join?<br>•Open to all locals and tourists of Tanay.<br>•This contest is open to entrants aged 16 and above.<br>(under 18 participants need to have a consent letter from their guardian)<br>•The participants must be presently residing in the Philippines.</p><p>Duration:<br>September 20 to October 20, 2018</p><p>Categories:<br><strong>Category: SELFIE&nbsp;</strong><br>A Selfie Photo Competition&nbsp;<br>• Like the Official Page of the Municipality of Tanay:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/\" data-mce-href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/\">https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/</a><br>• Take a creative selfie of yourself in any of Tanay Nature Tourist Destination.<br>• Selfies can only be submitted in the form of photo and not any other form of work.<br>• Only 1 entry per participant every month.<br>• Submitted photo must have a minimum file size of 1MB and maximum file size of 10MB<br>• The destination must be visible in the selfie.<br>• A selfie is considered any picture of yourself you can make holding the camera in hand or by using selfie stick or other related devices.<br>• A self portrait is not allowed and this is when put the camera on a tripod or any support to make the picture, controlling it with the remote shutter or the settings of your camera or by using drone and related devices.<br>• The photo must be taken year 2015-to present<br>• By submitting your entry, you agree that the materials sent will be automatically be a property of LGU Tanay<br>Photos must be submitted to:&nbsp;<span id=\"cloakeba3ec8139f8d67b037a71ecc34824e6\"><a href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\" data-mce-href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\">tanayphotocontest@gmail.com</a></span>&nbsp;with your Complete Name, Address, Contact Number, Age, Sex, Location of the Photo and Date taken. The email subject is “Tanay Photo Contest: Smile”</p><p><br><strong>Category: GROUPIE&nbsp;</strong><br>A Group Shot (Groupie) photography Competition.&nbsp;<br>• Like the Official Page of the Municipality of Tanay:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/\" data-mce-href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/\">https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/</a><br>• Take a creative Groupie of yourself or your friends in any of Tanay Nature Tourist Destination.<br>• Groupie can only be submitted in the form of photo and not any other form of work.<br>• Only 1 entry per participant every month.<br>• Submitted photo must have a minimum file size of 1MB and maximum file size of 10MB<br>• The destination must be visible in the groupie.<br>• Each person in the Group Shot entry must agree and have knowledge that the photo is submitted for this competition.<br>• The photo must be taken year 2015-to present<br>• By submitting your entry, you agree that the materials sent will be automatically be a property of LGU Tanay<br>Photos must be submitted to:&nbsp;<span id=\"cloakc162901c98351f211c6bc64bfd62c5ef\"><a href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\" data-mce-href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\">tanayphotocontest@gmail.com</a></span>&nbsp;with your Complete Name, Address, Contact Number, Age, Sex, Location of the Photo and Date taken. The email subject is “Tanay Photo Contest: Shine”</p><p><br><strong>Category: Tanay</strong><br>A conventional Photo Contest.&nbsp;<br>• Photo must be taken in any of Tanay Nature Tourist Destination<br>• The photo must be taken year 2015-to present.<br>• The photo must be in landscape size.<br>• Only 1 entry per participant every month.<br>• Submitted photo must have a minimum file size of 3MB and maximum file size of 20MB (300DPI)<br>• Only minimal editing is allowed. (Raw file must be submitted with exif file)<br>• No watermark<br>• By submitting your entry, you agree that the materials sent will be automatically be a property of LGU Tanay&nbsp;<br>• Entries also must be accompanied by a photo caption or words describing the photo’s content and story behind the photo. To be eligible for this contest.<br>• Cropped photos are eligible. Minor adjustments, including spotting, dodging and burning, sharpening, contrast and slight color adjustment or the digital equivalents, are acceptable. If the judges determine that a photographer has altered his or her photo, they reserve the right to move the photo to Altered Images or to disqualify it.<br>• For a photo in which a person is recognizable, you must secure a model letter of consent from the subject or, in the case of a minor, the subject’s parent or guardian and provide it to the Organizing Committee upon request.<br>• Entrants whose photos depict other people’s work (such as sculptures, statues, paintings, and other copyrightable works) may be need to obtain a release from the rights holder and provide it to the Organizing Committee upon request.&nbsp;<br>• When photographing the work of others, it must be as an object in its environment and not a full-frame close-up of another person\'s creation.&nbsp;<br>• Photographs that have won any other contests are not eligible to join the competition. We define “winning” as having won a grand prize or 1st, 2nd or 3rd place overall. Photos that violate or infringe upon another person\'s rights, including but not limited to copyright, are not eligible.<br>• Photos that contain sexually explicit, nude, obscene, violent or other objectionable or inappropriate content, as determined by the Organizing Committee in its sole discretion, are ineligible for this contest.</p><p>Photos must be submitted to:&nbsp;<span id=\"cloakdd1e87c60f8ba9f147d0a1d063920f2c\"><a href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\" data-mce-href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\">tanayphotocontest@gmail.com</a></span>&nbsp;with your Complete Name, Address, Contact Number, Age, Sex, Location of the Photo and Date taken. The email subject is “Tanay Photo Contest: Tanay”</p><p><strong>Copyright</strong><br>Photographers will retain full copyright over the submitted entries. However, they will authorize Municipal Government of Tanay to use the photos in any promotional campaign or materials without compensation or remuneration.</p><p><strong>Conditions of Entry</strong><br>• The Committee reserves the right to disqualify incomplete entries and/or contestants who are unable to submit upon request.<br>• The Committee may collect a photograph’s metadata upon entry.<br>• The Committee reserves the right to cancel the contest or modify these rules at its discretion. In the event of a dispute regarding the winners, the Committee reserves the right to award or not award the prizes in its sole discretion. The Committee reserves the right to disqualify any entrant whose entry or conduct appears in any way to: inhibit the enjoyment of others; tamper with the competition; violate these rules or other applicable law or regulation; infringe on the rights of third parties; or act in an unsportsmanlike or disruptive manner. Decisions of the Committee are final and binding.<br>• The Municipal Government of Tanay is not responsible for technical, hardware or software failures, or other errors or problems which may occur in connection with the Contest, whether computer, network, technical, mechanical, typographical, printing, human or otherwise, including, without limitation, errors or problems which may occur in connection with the administration of the Contest, the processing or judging of entries, the announcement of the prizes, in any Contest- related materials, or that may limit prize fulfillment or a participant\'s ability to enter the Contest. Sponsor reserve the right to amend these official rules and to permanently disqualify from the Contest any person it believes has intentionally violated these official rules.</p><p><br><strong>PRIVACY</strong>: By entering, you agree that the information you provide may be sent to promotional partners of the Sponsor. You may be contacted by Sponsor and/or promotional partners with future promotional offers. Information provided by you to participate in this Contest is subject to the privacy policies of the Sponsor.</p><p><br>Criteria for Judging:<br>1. Composition 25%<br>2. Creativity 25%<br>3. Image quality 25%<br>4. Over-all Impact 25%<br>TOTAL 100%</p><p><br>Winners:<br>Winners will announce before Hane Festival and the awarding would be on Gabi ng Parangal on November 11, 2018 in Tanay Municipal Grounds.</p><p><br>Prizes:&nbsp;<br>Grand Prize&nbsp;<br>Winner Category: SELFIE: Php 5,000<br>Winner Category: GROUPIE: Php 7,000<br>Winner Category: Tanay : Php 10,000</p><p><a href=\"https://tanay.gov.ph/announcements/569-join-now-tanay-photography-contest-2018\">https://tanay.gov.ph/announcements/569-join-now-tanay-photography-contest-2018</a></p><p><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p>', 'festival', '#PhotographyContest', 1, 4, '2018-10-03 10:58:18', 5, 1),
(17, 'LGU TANAY LAUNCHES ART EXHIBIT 2015', 'lgu-tanay-launches-art-exhibit-2015', '<p>In line with the celebration of the 5<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;Hane Festival, the Local Government Unit of Tanay through Tanay Tourism Office and in partnership with Tanay Artists Group formally launched the Art Exhibit 2015 with the theme “<em>Sining Imahinasyon at Kolaborasyon Para sa Ika-5 Selebrasyon”&nbsp;</em>at the 2<sup>nd</sup>&nbsp;floor of the Municipal Building, October 26.</p><p><img src=\"http://i430.photobucket.com/albums/qq25/lgutanay/Article/Picture2_zpskwj4zqlc.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" alt=\"\"><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p><p>Said art exhibit is the fifth year for the LGU to hold such event as part of the celebration of the festival. This year, more than 30 local visual artists collaborated and put their artworks on display.</p><p>Municipal Vice Mayor Jaime B. Vista, a member of Tanay Artists Group himself, said in his welcome remarks and rationale that the annual Hane Art Exhibit serves as an avenue for visual artists like him to showcase their talents and artistry. He noted further that the members of the artist group are thankful to Honorable Mayor Rafael A. Tanjuatco for acknowledging the group’s artistic endeavors.&nbsp;Likewise, Mr. Angelito Florendo, another member of the group, expressed his gratitude to all people who have supported them to realize this year’s exhibit.&nbsp;</p><p>Mayor Tanjuatco, meanwhile, conveyed his strong support to Tanay Artists Group as he believe they are partners of the local government, through the art pieces that they produce,&nbsp; in promoting Tanay – its tourism, environment, culture and tradition, and people. He said that the Hane Festival is&nbsp;an occasion to showcase many characteristics that are truly Tanay, thus the LGU is encouraging the participation of all the members of the community.</p><p>This year’s Art Exhibit will run from October 26-November 14, 2015. As of this writing, a number of paintings have already been sold after just a week.</p><p><img src=\"http://i430.photobucket.com/albums/qq25/lgutanay/Article/Picture1_zpse0hdaltm.png\" alt=\"Tanay Art Exhibit 2015\" data-mce-src=\"http://i430.photobucket.com/albums/qq25/lgutanay/Article/Picture1_zpse0hdaltm.png\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\"></p><p><a href=\"https://tanay.gov.ph/for-residents/news-events/122-lgu-tanay-launches-art-exhibit-2015\">https://tanay.gov.ph/for-residents/news-events/122-lgu-tanay-launches-art-exhibit-2015</a></p><p><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p>', 'festival', '#ArtExhibit', 1, 5, '2018-10-03 10:58:18', 5, 1);
