(44, 'TANAY PHOTOGRAPHY CONTEST 2017', 'tanay-photography-contest-2017', '<h2>TANAY PHOTOGRAPHY CONTEST 2017</h2><p><img src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/banners/tanay-photo-contest-2017.jpg\" alt=\"tanay photo contest 2017\" data-mce-src=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/images/banners/tanay-photo-contest-2017.jpg\" width=\"394\" height=\"253\"></p><p>Tanay Photography Contest 2017<br>This year 7th Tanay Hane Festival 2017 will highlight the beauty of Tanay from amateur photographer to pro-photographers. Three categories are open to all locals and tourist of Tanay.<br>Who are qualified to join?<br>•Open to all locals and tourists of Tanay.<br>•This contest is open to entrants aged 16 and above.<br>(under 18 participants need to have a consent letter from their guardian)<br>•The participants must be presently residing in the Philippines.</p><p>Duration:<br>September 5 to October 31, 2017</p><p>Categories:<br><strong>Category: Smile</strong><br>A Selfie Photo Competition&nbsp;<br>• Like the Official Page of the Municipality of Tanay:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/\" data-mce-href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/\">https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/</a><br>• Take a creative selfie of yourself in any of Tanay Nature Tourist Destination.<br>• It must be uploaded in Facebook or Instragram accessible by Public with Hashtag #TanayHaneFestivalSmile #SmileAndShineTanay<br>• Selfies can only be submitted in the form of photo and not any other form of work.<br>• Only 1 entry per participant every month.<br>• Submitted photo must have a minimum file size of 1MB and maximum file size of 10MB<br>• The destination must be visible in the selfie.<br>• A selfie is considered any picture of yourself you can make holding the camera in hand or by using selfie stick or other related devices.<br>• A self portrait is not allowed and this is when put the camera on a tripod or any support to make the picture, controlling it with the remote shutter or the settings of your camera or by using drone and related devices.<br>• The photo must be taken year 2015-to present<br>• By submitting your entry, you agree that the materials sent will be automatically be a property of LGU Tanay<br>Photos must be submitted to:&nbsp;<span id=\"cloak400ec346bd6cbeb39389ec63f8db7f43\"><a href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\" data-mce-href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\">tanayphotocontest@gmail.com</a></span>&nbsp;with your Complete Name, Address, Contact Number, Age, Sex, Location of the Photo and Date taken. The email subject is “Tanay Photo Contest: Smile”</p><p><br><strong>Category: Shine</strong><br>A Group Shot (Groupie) photography Competition.&nbsp;<br>• Like the Official Page of the Municipality of Tanay:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/\" data-mce-href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/\">https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/</a><br>• Take a creative Groupie of yourself or your friends in any of Tanay Nature Tourist Destination.<br>• It must be uploaded in Facebook or Instragram accessible by Public with Hashtag #TanayHaneFestivalShine #SmileAndShineTanay<br>• Groupie can only be submitted in the form of photo and not any other form of work.<br>• Only 1 entry per participant every month.<br>• Submitted photo must have a minimum file size of 1MB and maximum file size of 10MB<br>• The destination must be visible in the groupie.<br>• Each person in the Group Shot entry must agree and have knowledge that the photo is submitted for this competition.<br>• The photo must be taken year 2015-to present<br>• By submitting your entry, you agree that the materials sent will be automatically be a property of LGU Tanay<br>Photos must be submitted to:&nbsp;<span id=\"cloak19b5bb386e90be231b7e7d31744829b0\"><a href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\" data-mce-href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\">tanayphotocontest@gmail.com</a></span>&nbsp;with your Complete Name, Address, Contact Number, Age, Sex, Location of the Photo and Date taken. The email subject is “Tanay Photo Contest: Shine”</p><p><br><strong>Category: Tanay</strong><br>A conventional Photo Contest.&nbsp;<br>• Photo must be taken in any of Tanay Nature Tourist Destination<br>• The photo must be taken year 2015-to present.<br>• The photo must be in landscape size.<br>• Only 1 entry per participant every month.<br>• Submitted photo must have a minimum file size of 3MB and maximum file size of 20MB (300DPI)<br>• Only minimal editing is allowed. (Raw file must be submitted with exif file)<br>• No watermark<br>• By submitting your entry, you agree that the materials sent will be automatically be a property of LGU Tanay&nbsp;<br>• Entries also must be accompanied by a photo caption or words describing the photo’s content and story behind the photo. To be eligible for this contest.<br>• Cropped photos are eligible. Minor adjustments, including spotting, dodging and burning, sharpening, contrast and slight color adjustment or the digital equivalents, are acceptable. If the judges determine that a photographer has altered his or her photo, they reserve the right to move the photo to Altered Images or to disqualify it.<br>• For a photo in which a person is recognizable, you must secure a model letter of consent from the subject or, in the case of a minor, the subject’s parent or guardian and provide it to the Organizing Committee upon request.<br>• Entrants whose photos depict other people’s work (such as sculptures, statues, paintings, and other copyrightable works) may be need to obtain a release from the rights holder and provide it to the Organizing Committee upon request.&nbsp;<br>• When photographing the work of others, it must be as an object in its environment and not a full-frame close-up of another person\'s creation.&nbsp;<br>• Photographs that have won any other contests are not eligible to join the competition. We define “winning” as having won a grand prize or 1st, 2nd or 3rd place overall. Photos that violate or infringe upon another person\'s rights, including but not limited to copyright, are not eligible.<br>• Photos that contain sexually explicit, nude, obscene, violent or other objectionable or inappropriate content, as determined by the Organizing Committee in its sole discretion, are ineligible for this contest.</p><p>Photos must be submitted to:&nbsp;<span id=\"cloak527c7885680cca15ff6a5699038ea570\"><span id=\"cloak948484bb103ea900dd5e57e6fd3a9010\"><a href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\" data-mce-href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\">tanayphotocontest@gmail.com</a></span></span>&nbsp;with your Complete Name, Address, Contact Number, Age, Sex, Location of the Photo and Date taken. The email subject is “Tanay Photo Contest: Tanay”</p><p><strong>Copyright</strong><br>Photographers will retain full copyright over the submitted entries. However, they will authorize Municipal Government of Tanay to use the photos in any promotional campaign or materials without compensation or remuneration.</p><p><strong>Conditions of Entry</strong><br>• The Committee reserves the right to disqualify incomplete entries and/or contestants who are unable to submit upon request.<br>• The Committee may collect a photograph’s metadata upon entry.<br>• The Committee reserves the right to cancel the contest or modify these rules at its discretion. In the event of a dispute regarding the winners, the Committee reserves the right to award or not award the prizes in its sole discretion. The Committee reserves the right to disqualify any entrant whose entry or conduct appears in any way to: inhibit the enjoyment of others; tamper with the competition; violate these rules or other applicable law or regulation; infringe on the rights of third parties; or act in an unsportsmanlike or disruptive manner. Decisions of the Committee are final and binding.<br>• The Municipal Government of Tanay is not responsible for technical, hardware or software failures, or other errors or problems which may occur in connection with the Contest, whether computer, network, technical, mechanical, typographical, printing, human or otherwise, including, without limitation, errors or problems which may occur in connection with the administration of the Contest, the processing or judging of entries, the announcement of the prizes, in any Contest- related materials, or that may limit prize fulfillment or a participant\'s ability to enter the Contest. Sponsor reserve the right to amend these official rules and to permanently disqualify from the Contest any person it believes has intentionally violated these official rules.</p><p><br><strong>PRIVACY</strong>: By entering, you agree that the information you provide may be sent to promotional partners of the Sponsor. You may be contacted by Sponsor and/or promotional partners with future promotional offers. Information provided by you to participate in this Contest is subject to the privacy policies of the Sponsor.</p><p><br>Criteria for Judging:<br>1. Composition 25%<br>2. Creativity 25%<br>3. Image quality 25%<br>4. Over-all Impact 25%<br>TOTAL 100%</p><p><br>Winners:<br>Winners will announce before Hane Festival and the awarding would be on Gabi ng Parangal on November 12, 2017 in Tanay Municipal Grounds.</p><p><br>Prizes:&nbsp;<br>Grand Prize&nbsp;<br>Winner Category: Smile: Php 5,000<br>Winner Category: Shine: Php 7,000<br>Winner Category: Tanay : Php 10,000</p><p><a href=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/for-residents/news-events/349-tanay-photography-contest-2017\">http://tanay.gov.ph/for-residents/news-events/349-tanay-photography-contest-2017</a></p><p><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p>', 'festival', '#TanayPhotographyContest', 1, 8, '2018-10-03 10:58:18', 5, 1),
(45, 'JOIN NOW! TANAY PHOTOGRAPHY CONTEST 2018', 'join-now-tanay-photography-contest-2018', '<h2>JOIN NOW! TANAY PHOTOGRAPHY CONTEST 2018</h2><p>This year 8th Tanay Hane Festival 2018 will highlight the beauty of Tanay from amateur photographer to pro-photographers. Three categories are open to all locals and tourist of Tanay.</p><p><br>Who are qualified to join?<br>•Open to all locals and tourists of Tanay.<br>•This contest is open to entrants aged 16 and above.<br>(under 18 participants need to have a consent letter from their guardian)<br>•The participants must be presently residing in the Philippines.</p><p>Duration:<br>September 20 to October 20, 2018</p><p>Categories:<br><strong>Category: SELFIE&nbsp;</strong><br>A Selfie Photo Competition&nbsp;<br>• Like the Official Page of the Municipality of Tanay:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/\" data-mce-href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/\">https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/</a><br>• Take a creative selfie of yourself in any of Tanay Nature Tourist Destination.<br>• Selfies can only be submitted in the form of photo and not any other form of work.<br>• Only 1 entry per participant every month.<br>• Submitted photo must have a minimum file size of 1MB and maximum file size of 10MB<br>• The destination must be visible in the selfie.<br>• A selfie is considered any picture of yourself you can make holding the camera in hand or by using selfie stick or other related devices.<br>• A self portrait is not allowed and this is when put the camera on a tripod or any support to make the picture, controlling it with the remote shutter or the settings of your camera or by using drone and related devices.<br>• The photo must be taken year 2015-to present<br>• By submitting your entry, you agree that the materials sent will be automatically be a property of LGU Tanay<br>Photos must be submitted to:&nbsp;<span id=\"cloak5dc80f5f910a6b402cefde5f48201679\"><a href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\" data-mce-href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\">tanayphotocontest@gmail.com</a></span>&nbsp;with your Complete Name, Address, Contact Number, Age, Sex, Location of the Photo and Date taken. The email subject is “Tanay Photo Contest: Smile”</p><p><br><strong>Category: GROUPIE&nbsp;</strong><br>A Group Shot (Groupie) photography Competition.&nbsp;<br>• Like the Official Page of the Municipality of Tanay:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/\" data-mce-href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/\">https://www.facebook.com/tanayrizalgov/</a><br>• Take a creative Groupie of yourself or your friends in any of Tanay Nature Tourist Destination.<br>• Groupie can only be submitted in the form of photo and not any other form of work.<br>• Only 1 entry per participant every month.<br>• Submitted photo must have a minimum file size of 1MB and maximum file size of 10MB<br>• The destination must be visible in the groupie.<br>• Each person in the Group Shot entry must agree and have knowledge that the photo is submitted for this competition.<br>• The photo must be taken year 2015-to present<br>• By submitting your entry, you agree that the materials sent will be automatically be a property of LGU Tanay<br>Photos must be submitted to:&nbsp;<span id=\"cloak8cb15694bf9d2a574f111de182b11ef2\"><a href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\" data-mce-href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\">tanayphotocontest@gmail.com</a></span>&nbsp;with your Complete Name, Address, Contact Number, Age, Sex, Location of the Photo and Date taken. The email subject is “Tanay Photo Contest: Shine”</p><p><br><strong>Category: Tanay</strong><br>A conventional Photo Contest.&nbsp;<br>• Photo must be taken in any of Tanay Nature Tourist Destination<br>• The photo must be taken year 2015-to present.<br>• The photo must be in landscape size.<br>• Only 1 entry per participant every month.<br>• Submitted photo must have a minimum file size of 3MB and maximum file size of 20MB (300DPI)<br>• Only minimal editing is allowed. (Raw file must be submitted with exif file)<br>• No watermark<br>• By submitting your entry, you agree that the materials sent will be automatically be a property of LGU Tanay&nbsp;<br>• Entries also must be accompanied by a photo caption or words describing the photo’s content and story behind the photo. To be eligible for this contest.<br>• Cropped photos are eligible. Minor adjustments, including spotting, dodging and burning, sharpening, contrast and slight color adjustment or the digital equivalents, are acceptable. If the judges determine that a photographer has altered his or her photo, they reserve the right to move the photo to Altered Images or to disqualify it.<br>• For a photo in which a person is recognizable, you must secure a model letter of consent from the subject or, in the case of a minor, the subject’s parent or guardian and provide it to the Organizing Committee upon request.<br>• Entrants whose photos depict other people’s work (such as sculptures, statues, paintings, and other copyrightable works) may be need to obtain a release from the rights holder and provide it to the Organizing Committee upon request.&nbsp;<br>• When photographing the work of others, it must be as an object in its environment and not a full-frame close-up of another person\'s creation.&nbsp;<br>• Photographs that have won any other contests are not eligible to join the competition. We define “winning” as having won a grand prize or 1st, 2nd or 3rd place overall. Photos that violate or infringe upon another person\'s rights, including but not limited to copyright, are not eligible.<br>• Photos that contain sexually explicit, nude, obscene, violent or other objectionable or inappropriate content, as determined by the Organizing Committee in its sole discretion, are ineligible for this contest.</p><p>Photos must be submitted to:&nbsp;<span id=\"cloakf7fc060caa49d5f1d060b318ec8a8534\"><a href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\" data-mce-href=\"mailto:tanayphotocontest@gmail.com\">tanayphotocontest@gmail.com</a></span>&nbsp;with your Complete Name, Address, Contact Number, Age, Sex, Location of the Photo and Date taken. The email subject is “Tanay Photo Contest: Tanay”</p><p><strong>Copyright</strong><br>Photographers will retain full copyright over the submitted entries. However, they will authorize Municipal Government of Tanay to use the photos in any promotional campaign or materials without compensation or remuneration.</p><p><strong>Conditions of Entry</strong><br>• The Committee reserves the right to disqualify incomplete entries and/or contestants who are unable to submit upon request.<br>• The Committee may collect a photograph’s metadata upon entry.<br>• The Committee reserves the right to cancel the contest or modify these rules at its discretion. In the event of a dispute regarding the winners, the Committee reserves the right to award or not award the prizes in its sole discretion. The Committee reserves the right to disqualify any entrant whose entry or conduct appears in any way to: inhibit the enjoyment of others; tamper with the competition; violate these rules or other applicable law or regulation; infringe on the rights of third parties; or act in an unsportsmanlike or disruptive manner. Decisions of the Committee are final and binding.<br>• The Municipal Government of Tanay is not responsible for technical, hardware or software failures, or other errors or problems which may occur in connection with the Contest, whether computer, network, technical, mechanical, typographical, printing, human or otherwise, including, without limitation, errors or problems which may occur in connection with the administration of the Contest, the processing or judging of entries, the announcement of the prizes, in any Contest- related materials, or that may limit prize fulfillment or a participant\'s ability to enter the Contest. Sponsor reserve the right to amend these official rules and to permanently disqualify from the Contest any person it believes has intentionally violated these official rules.</p><p><br><strong>PRIVACY</strong>: By entering, you agree that the information you provide may be sent to promotional partners of the Sponsor. You may be contacted by Sponsor and/or promotional partners with future promotional offers. Information provided by you to participate in this Contest is subject to the privacy policies of the Sponsor.</p><p><br>Criteria for Judging:<br>1. Composition 25%<br>2. Creativity 25%<br>3. Image quality 25%<br>4. Over-all Impact 25%<br>TOTAL 100%</p><p><br>Winners:<br>Winners will announce before Hane Festival and the awarding would be on Gabi ng Parangal on November 11, 2018 in Tanay Municipal Grounds.</p><p><br>Prizes:&nbsp;<br>Grand Prize&nbsp;<br>Winner Category: SELFIE: Php 5,000<br>Winner Category: GROUPIE: Php 7,000<br>Winner Category: Tanay : Php 10,000</p><p><strong><a href=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/for-residents/news-events/349-tanay-photography-contest-2017\" data-mce-href=\"http://tanay.gov.ph/for-residents/news-events/349-tanay-photography-contest-2017\">http://tanay.gov.ph/for-residents/news-events/349-tanay-photography-contest-2017</a></strong></p>', 'festival', '#PhotographyContest', 1, 7, '2018-10-03 10:58:18', 5, 1),
(46, 'TANAY LGU LAUNCHES SABAWAN NIGHTS', 'tanay-lgu-launches-sabawan-nights', '<h2>TANAY LGU LAUNCHES SABAWAN NIGHTS</h2><p>As part of promoting Tanay Hane Festival 2015, the local government of Tanay, through Liga ng mga Barangay (LnB) President Hon. Ruel P. Estrella, launched Sabawan Nights 2015 on Oct. 23 at Yujuico St. in Tanay Park.</p><p>In his rationale, Municipal Administrator Gabriel C. Piguing explained that the nightly activity – which will run from October 23 to November 11 – is meant to serve as a means of bonding for Tanayans.</p><p>Meanwhile, Mayor Rafael A. Tanjuatco stressed that Sabawan Nights is also a way of showcasing Tanay’s delicacies and cuisine. He also said that the event is designed to draw tourists to the municipality as part of the many activities of Tanay Hane Festival 2015.</p><p>Sabawan Nights features live bands, as well as food and beverages stalls where residents and tourists can enjoy affordable food and drinks.</p><p>Various barangays and organizations take turns in hosting the nightly sabawan events, which are steadily attracting Tanayans and residents from neighboring municipalities.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"http://www.tanay.gov.ph/8-news-events/116-tanay-lgu-launches-sabawan-nights\">http://www.tanay.gov.ph/8-news-events/116-tanay-lgu-launches-sabawan-nights</a></p><p><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p>', 'festival', '#SabawanNights', 1, 9, '2018-10-03 10:58:18', 5, 1),
(47, 'HISTORY AND CULTURE', 'history-and-culture', '<div><div>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tanay,_Rizal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-mce-href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tanay,_Rizal\">Tanay</a>&nbsp;is a municipality in Rizal. It is very known for it\'s wonderful treasures. These treasures are places that can be seen in Tanay which is one of a kind. Some of them are the Daranak Falls, Regina Rica, Masungi Rock, Parola, Tanay Church, Kinabuan Falls and Tinipak Rock.<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Another attraction of Tanay is the Hane Festival. The Festival is honored for the foundation of Tanay. It is started from November 12 the day the town is founded and it goes on for few days.</div></div><div><div>In the Festival we can see the cultures of Tanay. The festival got its name from the word \"HANE\" a word meaning ok.&nbsp;</div></div><div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The History of Tanay dates back from the 1700. It was first named \"Monte de Tan-ay\". People who first lived here had to fight for their freedom against the Spaniards. In 1947, Tanay established their Barangays they were&nbsp;Nuestra Senora del Rosario, Sa Josep, San Ildefonso de Tanay, San Francisco de Maytubig, San Pedro de Alcantara, San Lucas y San Antonio, San Apostol and San Agustin de Balugbog. In 1894 Tanay was officially declared as a Municipality.</div><div><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></div><div>http://andreisaberdo.blogspot.com/2014/09/history-and-culture-of-tanay.html</div></div>', 'culture', '#HaneCulture', 1, 4, '2018-10-03 10:58:18', 3, 1),
(48, 'JUST ANOTHER WIN FOR CUM LAUDE IN WHEECHAIR', 'just-another-win-for-cum-laude-in-wheechair', '<p><img src=\"http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/files/2018/06/20180623lr4-620x396.jpg\" data-mce-src=\"http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/files/2018/06/20180623lr4-620x396.jpg\" width=\"375\" height=\"250\"></p><p>In the sea of some 4,600 graduates of the University of the Philippines (UP) Diliman on Sunday, Alexander Michael Bautista easily stands out, and not just because he uses a wheelchair.</p><p>Graduation for this business administration major marks another win against seemingly endless odds that started when he was 2 and diagnosed with spinal muscular atrophy (SMA), a rare neuromuscular disorder with no known cure that affects control of muscle movement.</p><p>But Miggy, as friends and family call him, was not one to be defined by limitations.</p><p>“Who would have thought I would graduate, and from UP Diliman no less?” the 20-year-old cum laude chuckled.</p><p>But like raising a child, it takes a village — in this case, the entire UP community — to literally carry Miggy through his academic journey.</p><p>It certainly helped that his parents, Gabriel and Soledad, were very hands-on in their support.</p><p>The couple had perfected their four-year routine: Wake up as early as 5 a.m. and travel for around two hours from their home in Tanay, Rizal province, to get their son to school in Quezon City, carry Miggy to the car, transfer him to the wheelchair, and wheel him to his classes in different buildings inside the UP campus.</p><p>Read more:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1003564/just-another-win-for-up-cum-laude-in-wheelchair#ixzz5T4RyUMGy\" data-mce-href=\"https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1003564/just-another-win-for-up-cum-laude-in-wheelchair#ixzz5T4RyUMGy\">https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1003564/just-another-win-for-up-cum-laude-in-wheelchair#ixzz5T4RyUMGy</a>&nbsp;<br>Follow us:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://ec.tynt.com/b/rw?id=bSAw-mF-0r4Q-4acwqm_6r&amp;u=inquirerdotnet\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-mce-href=\"http://ec.tynt.com/b/rw?id=bSAw-mF-0r4Q-4acwqm_6r&amp;u=inquirerdotnet\">@inquirerdotnet on Twitter</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://ec.tynt.com/b/rf?id=bSAw-mF-0r4Q-4acwqm_6r&amp;u=inquirerdotnet\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-mce-href=\"http://ec.tynt.com/b/rf?id=bSAw-mF-0r4Q-4acwqm_6r&amp;u=inquirerdotnet\">inquirerdotnet on Facebook</a></p>', 'people', '#UPCUMLAUDE', 1, 2, '2018-10-05 15:31:00', 4, 1),
